items.text:
# Atem- und Sprechtechnik

Atem- und Sprechtechnik: Entfalte deine volle Ausdruckskraft!

 

Möchtest du:

 

- Klarheit in deiner Stimme erreichen?

- Eine korrekte Aussprache entwickeln?

- Deinen Akzent reduzieren oder akzentfrei sprechen?

- Deinen Dialekteinfluss vermindern?

- Deutlich artikulieren?

- Eine überzeugende Rhetorik beherrschen?

- Frei und selbstbewusst sprechen?

- Verständlich formulieren?

- Wirksam präsentieren?

- Kompetent argumentieren?

- Überzeugend rezitieren (Sachtexte, Prosa, Lyrik, Dramatik usw.)?

- Einfach richtig und gut Deutsch sprechen?

- Ein Medientraining absolvieren?

- Eine Atmung erlernen, die all das ermöglicht?

 

Wenn du nur eine dieser Fragen mit "Ja" beantworten kannst, dann findest du hier alles, was du dafür brauchst.

 

**Und das sagen Teilnehmer*innen (Auswahl):**

Die Testimonials sind aus Datenschutzgründen anonymisiert. Du willst noch mehr Testimonials oder solche, die nicht anonysmisiert sind? Dann lese die Bewertungen auf **[Google](https://www.google.ch/maps/place/ZES+Zentrum+f%C3%BCr+Entwicklung+im+Schauspiel/@47.509748,8.5949863,17z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m5!3m4!1s0x479a9e1995257499:0x6e04509e633044c9!8m2!3d47.509748!4d8.597175)**.

***„Vielen Dank für das Training letzte Woche. Ich habe inzwischen weiter geübt und es fällt mir schon wesentlich leichter mit dem S und fühlt sich natürlicher an.“ R.***

***„Deine Hilfe, Unterstützung und Unterricht gefallen mir sehr. Somit freue ich mich auf die weitere Zusammenarbeit.*** ***Auch ich arbeite sehr gerne mit Dir zusammen.“ T.***

***„Vielen Dank für das ehrliche und konstruktive Feedback!“ K.***

 

Über den Trainer: 

Marco Hausammann-Gilardi bringt mehr als 40 Jahre Erfahrung als Schauspieler, Autor, Regisseur und Produzent in Theater, Film und Fernsehen mit. Er arbeitete zudem als Moderator, Journalist und Redakteur für Radio und Fernsehen, als Sprecher für Werbung, Voice-Over und Synchron (Voice-Artist) und führte Fernseh- und Tonstudioregie.

 

Nutze diese einzigartige Gelegenheit, um deine kommunikativen Fähigkeiten auf das nächste Level zu heben!

 

Der private Unterricht ist persönlich oder via Zoom möglich.

 

Du willst es genau wissen. Auf der Website findest du alles, was du brauchst:

•          Alle Details

•          Testimonials / Bewertungen

•          Die Anmeldung

 

ZES Zentrum für Entwicklung im Schauspiel Zürich

 

[https://zes-info.ch/atem-und-sprechtechnik/](https://zes-info.ch/atem-und-sprechtechnik/)

***„Deine Hilfe, Unterstützung und Unterricht gefallen mir sehr. Somit freue ich mich auf die weitere Zusammenarbeit.*** ***Auch ich arbeite sehr gerne mit Dir zusammen.“ T.***

***„Vielen Dank für das ehrliche und konstruktive Feedback!“ K.***

 

Über den Trainer: 

Marco Hausammann-Gilardi bringt mehr als 40 Jahre Erfahrung als Schauspieler, Autor, Regisseur und Produzent in Theater, Film und Fernsehen mit. Er arbeitete zudem als Moderator, Journalist und Redakteur für Radio und Fernsehen, als Sprecher für Werbung, Voice-Over und Synchron (Voice-Artist) und führte Fernseh- und Tonstudioregie.

 

Nutze diese einzigartige Gelegenheit, um deine kommunikativen Fähigkeiten auf das nächste Level zu heben!

 

Der private Unterricht ist persönlich oder via Zoom möglich.

 

Du willst es genau wissen. Auf der Website findest du alles, was du brauchst:

•          Alle Details

•          Testimonials / Bewertungen

•          Die Anmeldung

 

ZES Zentrum für Entwicklung im Schauspiel Zürich

items.title: Poszukujemy:

items.text:
Hej, 

Do reklamy napoju energetycznego poszukuję.

1. Pana grającego konkretnie w urban golfa w wieku 18-70 lat, którego wizerunek jest trochę bardziej niegrzeczny. Pan będzie stał tyłem więc całkowita stawka to 2500 zł. 
2. Starszej Babci w wieku 60-80 lat ale chętnie Pani będzie wiarygodna w roli Pani ze wsi. Pani musi być mimo wszystko sprawna fizycznie i mieć odpowiednią. STAWKA dla Pani : dniówka + 2500 zł za prawa. Bardzo mile widziane też Panie statystki. 

Proszę o wysyłanie wizytówek na YouTube do mnie do czwartku do godziny 16.00. 

Proszę pilnować aby każdy wpisywał agencję.

items.text:
CASTING CALL/ NON-UNION 

Casting Russian speaking roles in the short anti-war film 'During Winter, I Thought of My Father' written and directed by Danill Vasilyev. 

Please submit resume, headshot(s), and demo reel (if applicable) to duringwinter26@gmail.com to receive sides. 

Audition submission deadline: OCTOBER 18, 2025

Character descriptions below: 

ARTYOM

Russian speaking man, early 20s.

Description: Having seen the horrors of war firsthand, this young man became a conscientious objector who deserted the war. And despite paying a high price for his decision, losing a leg to frostbite, Artyom remains entrenched in his anti-war beliefs. A bright young

man from a middle-class family, who loves poetry and shoemaking, Artyom uses every ounce of his physical and mental might to get back to his family. 

VLADIMIR 

Russian speaking man, 50s-60s. 

A staunch patriot who was once a soldier too. A decorated one, whose pride in his heroic exploits for the Motherland could be felt from afar. But now, the old man stands alone. No family, no friends, no backing from the state which he holds so dear. His only son died

in a war years ago. All that’s left is the inextinguishable belief in his national identity, which has been built from years of tradition and pride. 

Rate: Unpaid, travel and food will be provided as well as top billing credits and IMDB credit.

items.text:
Model • Performer • TV-Erfahrung

Ich stehe noch am Anfang aber ich liebe, Ausdruck und Wandelbarkeit – vor der Kamera, auf der Bühne und in jeder Produktion. Mit Pole Dance und Tanz vereine ich Eleganz, Stärke und kreative Energie. Jede Bewegung, jeder Look erzählt eine Geschichte – von sinnlich bis kraftvoll.

Instagram:Jx.anie

Meine TV-Auftritte als Komparse (Berlin – Tag & Nacht, Anwälte im Einsatz, Auf Streife) haben mir zusätzliche Präsenz und Kamera-Sicherheit gegeben. Für Fashion, Beauty, Werbung & kreative Kooperationen bringe ich Professionalität, Leidenschaft und Persönlichkeit mit.

📩 Anfragen für Model-Jobs & Werbung: DM oder Mail.

items.text:
In Living Colored Inc, a 501c3 social justice theater casting 2 Males and 1 Female. 25-45 

Performances are in November in Educational Settings for talkback audiences.

Fort Collins.

It is a satirical comedy about 4 white woke people creating a play explaining Thanksgiving to middle school students. Without offending Native Americans.

Larissa FastHorse is the first Native American to have a play produced on Broadway. 

There will be a cast -audience talkbacks led by A Lakota Woman.

"Should THANKSGIVING be a National Holiday or a National Day of Mourning?

Rehearsals start 13th of October. Tues-Friday.

We will schedule when we have cast availability.

Rehearsals are 2 hours.

The running time of the piece is 75 minutes.

Performances are the 10th, 11th, 12 of November 

Front Range Community College 

11-1.   With student Talk back 

Campuses in Fort Collins, Boulder, Westminster.

Performances 14th 15th of November Foco Cultural Enrichment Center 7:00pm  

With Audience Talk back

All Saints Episcopal Church in Loveland 

November 22nd 7:00 performance 

We comply with a Colorado Theater Standards

Pay is 500.00. 

Contact Michael Anthony Tatmon 

mat@inlivingcolored.com

Text 970-714-6534 personal 

970-820-7264 Business

items.text:
📣 **Casting & Crew Call – Indie Horror Short** 🎬

**Project:** Independent horror short film for submission to the *Jakob Owens Horror Film Festival*
**Director:** *Sidney Cara*
**Producer:** *Legacy Landmarks Studio / Sidney Cara*

**Date:** **Monday, October 6th, 12 PM – 7 PM**
**Location:** Lorson Ranch (Fountain, CO)

We’re seeking:
🧟 **Extras as Zombies** – SFX make-up & fake blood applied on set
🎤 **Boom Operator** – Experience preferred, but not required
🎬 **Production Assistant (PA)** – On-set support
📸 **BTS Photographer** – Canon 90D camera provided, just need to capture behind-the-scenes photos

This is a **small indie project (low-budget, unpaid/credit + IMDb)**, great for experience, networking, and portfolio material. Food and drinks will be provided on set.

If interested, please message me directly or email:
📧 legacylandmarksstudio@gmail.com

Thank you for helping bring this project to life!
— **Legacy Landmarks Studio** 🎬

[Nieaktualne]

Casting!

​[Gdańsk]

Szukam tancerki (tancerki/aktorki) do spektaklu Lilije; to mroczny i epicki spektakl dramatyczno-taneczny na podstawie ballady Mickiewicza z tańcem, grą na instrumentach i śpiewem wieloglosowym na żywo.

Tu zwiastun: [https://youtube.com/shorts/QoVYI9z-c0E?si=vL0OseuQpHg_DtLT](https://youtube.com/shorts/QoVYI9z-c0E?si=vL0OseuQpHg_DtLT)

Tu więcej informacji: [https://www.facebook.com/share/18bUFBgxwr/](https://www.facebook.com/share/18bUFBgxwr/)

Rola zasadniczo bez te​kstu; kilka linijek mówionych wspólnie ze wszystkimi. Umiejętność śpiewu, szczególnie na biało, będzie dużym atutem. Taniec współczesny, improwizacja, teatr tańca są wymagane.

Projekt non-profit, próby w październiku i listopadzie w poniedziałki od 19:30-21:30 w ACK UG. Spektakle płatne, w tym roku grania 7 i 14 grudnia. 

Premiera odbyła się w czerwcu, spektakl cieszył się dużym zainteresowaniem.

Zgłoszenie prześlij na [weronikakamola@gmail.com](mailto:weronikakamola@gmail.com), a w nim:

- ​zdjęcie, wzrost i wiek

- opis swojego doświadczenia tanecznego i śpiewaczego 

- filmik, na którym widać, jak tańczysz

sharedPost.text:
Film zostanie wysłany na ogolnolicealny Fresh Form film festiwal, sa dwie reżyserki, w tym ja, z małym doświadczeniem ale wielkim zapałem. Mamy kamerę i stroje. Nie jest to płatne, można powiedzieć hobbistyczne, ale na pewno będzie to ciekawa przygoda. Okolice Warszawy, Piaseczna. Dni nagrywek są elastyczne 

Film jest obyczajowy, opowiada o grupie nastolatków zmagających się z problemami w rodzinie, z używkami i chorobą. Film opiera się na scenach rozmów, drogi i ‚gonitwy’. jest bardzo emocjonalny i pełen pasji.

Fajnie jakby zgłoszeni mieli styl bliski alternatywnemu, rockowemu (wielkim plusem byłaby umiejętność gry na gitarze) Szukamy przede wszystkim chłopaka 170-190cm z kręconymi włosami, grający rolę najlepszego przyjaciela głównego bohatera który stara się pomóc w leczeniu jego matki.

Poboczne role to postać chłopaka o podobnym wzroście, jasne proste lub falowane włosy, oraz jeszcze dwójki chłopaków, bez większych wymagań (jeden lepiej by było jakby miał długie włosy, hipisowski styl)

Naprawdę doceniam każdego chętnego, jesteśmy bardzo zaangażowane w tworzenie, a scenariusz jest naprawdę ambitny.

items.text:
📣🎬 Casting Call – Short Mockumentary Film 

We are casting for ‘A Race with Ian Hitchworth’, a 3-minute mockumentary short film made as part of our final year at UWE Bristol. The film will be shot in Bristol in the week commencing 3rd November 2025 (exact dates TBC). This is a student project, unpaid, but with expenses covered. The film is intended for university showcase and festival submission.

Story:�Ian Hitchworth, son of a respected track runner, was once a rising sprint star. Years later, he resurfaces in a humiliating viral TikTok, and a small documentary crew captures his desperate bid to matter again—culminating in a shambolic charity race. Told in a deadpan, mockumentary style, the film mixes awkward comedy with moments of vulnerability as Ian’s arrogance clashes with his insecurities.

Roles:
Ian Hitchworth (Lead)�25, male. Wannabe track star with inflated self-belief and fragile confidence. To the camera, he’s arrogant, overconfident, and insists on being taken seriously — but cracks show through awkward silences and moments of panic. Actor must have strong comedic timing, improvisational instincts, and be comfortable with physical comedy (running, awkward costume, frustrated energy). Needs to balance deadpan humour with flashes of real vulnerability.

Interviewer (Supporting)�Any age/gender. Calm, inquisitive presence behind the camera, provoking Ian with offhand questions and blunt corrections. Think Nick Broomfield style: slightly awkward, matter-of-fact, not intentionally funny but often humorous through honesty. Delivery should be dry and understated. Voice-only, but may appear briefly on camera.

Race Official / Athletes (Supporting & Extras)�18–40, any gender. Includes a race official who ushers Ian onto the track (Small Speaking Role), plus authentic-looking athletes for the race sequence. Non-speaking, but must look natural on a track.

Apply by: 27th Ocotber 2025�To Apply: Please send a headshot, CV (or Spotlight/Mandy link), and any showreel/self-tape to Scarlet2.Gerry@live.uwe.ac.uk

Needs strong comedic timing, improvisational skills, and comfort with physical comedy. Interviewer (Supporting) Dry, deadpan delivery. Provides calm contrast to lan's chaotic Race Official/ Athletes (Supporting & Extras) 18-40, any gender. Includes race official and background runners. Must look on track. dates Seeking contributors voluntarily travel expenses and food will be provided. Toapply send headshots &CV'sto'

items.text:
Two weeks from today, October 22 live and in person!! Mission 1 Billion meeting Wednesday, October 22, 7pm at Schmidty’s  Bar and Grill in Brookfield. Come early and stay late so we could begin on time.. Share with your filmmaker and actor friends.

Rocky Wagonhurst’s five-decade journey through the world of media is nothing short of extraordinary. He began in the 1970s as a Universal Studios tour guide and went on to appear on The Young and the Restless, star in national commercials, and play Laertes in a five-hour production of Hamlet. He was also directed by Steven Spielberg in Minority Report alongside Tom Cruise and once soared 10,000 feet above Lake Tahoe in a glider with actor Cliff Robertson. His career has spanned radio, stage, and screen, ultimately leading him behind the camera as a seasoned television executive. Currently, Rocky serves as Vice President and General Manager of The CW and My24 stations in Milwaukee, bringing his lifelong passion for storytelling and media innovation to local broadcasting. 

Mark your calendar now and we will see you then! Look for us on FB too @everyone  

ENTER  the door under the White Claw sign

Please share ! Help us spread the word this is open to the public.

items.text:
So proud to be the Executive Producer and Casting Director on Taro O'Halloran’s Short Horror Film  HUMANZEE starring Liz Bishop, Cheryl Pynn and introducing Zach Norton as Ziggy!! 

It is screening at Screamfest Horror Film Festival in Hollywood at Mann’s Chinese Theatre!

sharedPost.text:
Congratulations to Taro O'Halloran of Weymouth High School Class of 2020 on the screening of his Short Horror Film Humanzee starring Liz Bishop, Cheryl Pynn and introducing Zach Norton of Weymouth at Screamfest Horror Film Festival at the @TCL Chinese Theater in Hollywood!  

I am so honored to have the titles of Executive Producer and Casting Director on this film!

The hope is someone will see it and want to develop it into a Full Length Feature Film!

I see this film bringing home some awards!

My fingers are crossed for Taro’s Team!

Thank you Diane Purdy's Children's Theatre Workshop for giving me my own Stage from 9 to 49 and for letting me pass it on to John and Jake who brought Taro home from school one day and we all collaborated on multiple video productions with Diane’s costumes for years! 

https://2025screamfest.eventive.org/films/68d1b14f6ac811912ea77b5c?fbclid=IwZXh0bgNhZW0CMTEAAR6Vy5trrNroF8v33cSuHpp_m2mf0qAtnnMljE9_T7BIh64lBOdHCOJWfuCTlQ_aem_eM-d05jAN52my1WjOr_zoQ

Looking for models in LA to submit ASAP! Register to apply ASAP at chaarmzmagazine.com/talentsignup for the following:

Project: HIGH FASHION LIVE EVENT
Location: Los Angeles
Rate: $350 US (minus agency commissions)
Union: Non-Union 
Audition Type: Self Tape/ Virtual
Stand-In | Any Gender | 20 - 40 | Any Ethnic Appearance

Project Synopsis: We are looking for skilled character actors to be apart of a Live Fashion Event in LA. Please see each roles for specifics. This is a live in person event - it will be live streamed on Youtube. All talent confirmed will be required to attend a fitting w/o 20th oct, a rehearsal day 25th Oct, and the event day 26th Oct. in L.A.
 
Register at chaarmzmagazine.com/talentsignup and put your profile link and instagram links under ‘profile link’ and also mention which role you’re applying for. 

We need your application ASAP to submit. Thank you and good luck!

Chaarmz Talent Agency

Hallo zusammen!

Ich plane einen kurzen Liebes-Drama mit Spannungselementen, bei dem es um Vertrautheit, Gefühle und einen Bösewicht geht. 🌹🖤

Für dieses Projekt suche ich Studenten oder junge Filmemacher, die Lust haben, technisch und kreativ mitzuwirken – sei es Kamera, Ton, Licht oder Produktionssupport. Equipment ist natürlich super, aber genauso wichtig ist Motivation und Spaß am Drehen.

items.text:
Hallo Zusammen, 

ich suche für einen Fernsehbeitrag für das ZDF eine Protagonistin zwischen 35 und 50, die Lust hat, einige Hyaluronprodukte für uns auszuprobieren. Es ist leider etwas spontan: Der Dreh ist übermorgen, am Donnerstag, 9.10., in der Nähe von Mainz, für etwa zwei-zweieinhalb Stunden um die Mittagszeit. Bei Interesse schreibt mir gerne direkt eine Nachricht:-) Liebe Grüße, Corinna

items.text:
My name is Luke Kenyon, and I’m a film student at SAE Liverpool. We’re currently working on a new short film project titled Last Night and are looking to cast two male-identifying actors to join our team. This project is Non paid but we will be providing travel expenses as well as catering 

Synopsis -

On the anniversary of his best friend’s suicide, Aaron plans to end his own life. He ignores his mothers phone calls and edges closer towards his own end, until he unexpectedly hears a knock at his apartment front door. His best friend, Ben, appears in an attempt to make amends and guide Aaron away from darkness. This intimate drama, through one final, raw conversation, forces Aaron to choose between following the same path that Ben took a year ago, or answering the call that could save him.

If you have any questions about the project or roles, please don’t hesitate to get in touch — I’m happy to provide more information.

If you  are interested in applying, please use one of the provided links below or alternatively email me at 120206uk@saeinstitute.edu with your details, previous work, or portfolio. (Including heat shots)

Thank you very much for your time We look forward to hearing from you!

Kind regards,

Luke Kenyon

Film Student, SAE Institute

https://www.backstage.com/casting/last-night-student-film-3019197/

https://www.starnow.com/casting/last-night-3021254/

https://www.mandy.com/aa/project/3021242/last-night/

items.text:
My name is Adelola Mary Haastrup, and I’m a passionate actress currently based in Nigeria. I’m looking to expand my career in the UK and am actively seeking opportunities for visa sponsorship.

I started acting at the age of 7, performing in stage productions. While much of my early work was in gospel theater, I’m not particularly religious, and my focus has always been on the craft of acting. I’m eager to explore a wide range of roles in film, TV, theater, and commercial work, and I’m excited to branch out into new genres and experiences.

In addition to my acting experience, I studied Music Technology with a major in Stage Performing Arts for 2 years , and I have full documentation of all my final projects from that time. This technical training complements my stage performance and has given me a comprehensive understanding of both the artistic and technical sides of the industry.

I was also part of a gospel drama group form 2011 to 2020 , where I won 4 "Card Awards," including Best Actress  (twice), Best Dressed, and Best Minister. These awards reflect my dedication to the craft, and I’m incredibly proud of them.

I’m looking forward to collaborating on a wide range of acting roles in the UK’s vibrant and inclusive creative industry, and I’m actively seeking potential employers who are willing to support visa sponsorships for skilled performers like me.

If you have any leads or know of any production companies, agents, or casting opportunities, I would love to hear from you! Please feel free to DM me or comment below.

Thank you so much for your time and consideration. I look forward to connecting with you all!

sharedPost.text:
Der Kino Mittwoch auf radioYpsilon 

MOVIETIME KW 41/2025

EIN KULTKLASSIKER FEIERT SEINEN 40er UND EIN  LANGFILMCOMEBACK MADE IN AUSTRIA 

Nach 10jähriger Unterbrechung feiert Regisseur Andreas Prochaska mit WELCOME HOME BABY seine Langfilmrückkehr und ist bei uns im Interview zu hören.

Vor 43 Jahren startete das Franchise und kehrt mit TRON: ARES aktuell in die Kino zurück.

Die letzten Kriegstage des 2. WK auf einer Insel in Deutschland erzählt uns sensibel AMRUM von Regisseur Fatih Akin, der uns ein paar Worte spendete. 

Ausserdem feiert der Fluxkompensator einen runden Geburtstag. 

Abgerundet mit weiteren Film Highlights und Musik aus Filmen der letzten 80 Jahre begleitet Sie Sarah Fuchs durch die Sendung. 

Mittwoch 8.10.25 von 18 bis 19h auf radioYpsilon 94.5 oder via Stream (http://mp3.radioypsilon.at:8000/)

items.text:
**Looking for 4 actors/actresses**

Hey everyone! 
We’re looking for **4 people who’d like to act** in a **camera and directing exercise** at our film school.
No previous experience needed, just enthusiasm and a willingness to collaborate.

**What it’s about:**
We’ll be working on **short dialogue scenes**, each focused on **a specific emotion**. The exercise will explore **camera movement** and how actors and directors adapt to each other, just like in a film, but with short and experimental scenes.

The scenes can be performed in **English or German**, depending on what you feel most comfortable with.

🗓 **Date:** October 16th
🕙 **Time:** 10:00–16:00
📍 **Location:** FilmArche 

It’ll be a fun and creative day of learning and collaboration.
If you’re interested or know someone who might be, send me a message!

items.text:
**WARSZAWA **

**10, 11, 13, 14 października**

**film fabularny**

Na kolejne dni filmu **JAN BO** i już jedne z ostatnich szukam Statystów jak poniżej. Przeczytajcie proszę uważnie wytyczne charakteryzacji.

**10 PAŹDZIERNIKA (piątek):**
* **MŁODZIEŻ NA PRÓBIE MUZYCZNEJ 18-25 LAT **- jedna scena, wnętrze. Głównie dziewczyny. Stawka: 120 zł gotówka po planie

**11 PAŹDZIERNIKA (sobota):**
* **POKOJÓWKA**- kobieta ok. 30-40 lat. Stawka 180 zł gotówką po planie (przymiarki stacjonarne: 60 zł + 120 zł za dzień zdjęciowy). Przymiarki w piątek 10.10 na Chełmskiej po 14:00 

**13 PAŹDZIERNIKA (poniedziałek):**
* **GOŚCIE BARU / PRZECHODNIE - wiek ok. 20-55 lat. **Jedna scena, godziny popołudniowe.** **Stawka 120 zł gotówką po planie
* **STRAŻNICY GRANICZNI - mężczyźni ok. 30-50 lat**. Jedna scena. Poproszę wymiary w zgłoszeniu. Stawka 140 zł gotówką po planie
* **STRAŻNIK GRANICZNY Z OWCZARKIEM NIEMIECKIM **- jak wyżej. Jedna scena. Stawka 180 zł gotówką po planie.
* **KELNERKA **- **kobieta ok. 20-35 lat**.Jedna scena. Stawka 120 zł gotówką po planie

**14 PAŹDZIERNIKA (wtorek):**
* **KOBIETA NA SPACERZE Z PSEM** - wiek bez znaczenia. Psiak nie może być rasowy. Kundle będą najlepsze. Poproszę zdjęcie psa również. **Jedna scena nocna. 240 zł przelewem**

Ponieważ gramy lata 80te mamy nieuniknione wytyczne charakteryzacji:

**Dla wszystkich:**
* brak tatuaży w widocznych miejscach (ręce również, na nogach u pań też odpadają)
* bez tuneli w uszach
* kolczyki w nosie, brwiach czy wardze trzeba wyjąć na zdjęcia

**Panowie:**
* bez wygolonych boków i bez włosów ścinanych maszynką, bez zarostów od barbera
* długie włosy super
* łysi panowie niestety odpadają

**Panie:**
* paznokcie TYLKO naturalne. 
* bez permanentnych makijaży, doklejonych rzęs i innych ingerencji współczesnych kosmetologii

**ZGŁOSZENIA**

Poproszę na adres: **dominika@podtytulem.pl**

W tytule: **JB + wybrane daty**

W treści: imię i nazwisko, wiek, nr telefonu, miejscowość + wymiary: wzrost, klatka, pas, biodra, rozmiar ubrania i buta

W załączniku: ZDJĘCIE TWARZY I SYLWETKI: tylko z dnia zgłoszenia.

Portretowe selfie w dziennym świetle, na wprost, patrząc w obiektyw. Bez żadnych filtrów. Bez okularów. Bez nakrycia głowy.

Panie - bez makijażu, w rozpuszczonych włosach tak, żeby widoczna była długość włosów

Panowie - dodatkowo zdjęcie z profilu

attachments.ocrText: May be an image of 3 people and text that says 'SZUKAMY STATYSTÓW! Film "Jan Bo" 10-11-12-13-14.10 10-11-12 Warszawa Panie i Panowie 18-55 lat Zgłoszenia na adres dominika dominika@podtytulem.pl PODI TYTUŁEM'

items.text:
**WARSZAWA **

**11 października**

**EPIZODY - 300 zł**

Na plan filmu **JAN BO** szukam **bardzo atrakcyjnych dziewczyn ok. 20 - 30 lat.**

Sceny w hotelu z zespołem. Bez kontrowersji. Impreza. Dziewczyny tańczą.

Ponieważ gramy lata 80te mamy nieuniknione wytyczne charakteryzacji:
* brak tatuaży 
* bez piercingu
* paznokcie tylko naturalne. 
* bez permanentnych makijaży, doklejonych rzęs i innych ingerencji współczesnych kosmetologii

**ZGŁOSZENIA**

Poproszę na adres: **ewelina.wika@podtytulem.pl**

W tytule: **JBE 11**

W treści: imię i nazwisko, wiek, nr telefonu, miejscowość + wymiary: wzrost, klatka, pas, biodra, rozmiar ubrania i buta

W załączniku: ZDJĘCIE TWARZY I SYLWETKI: tylko z dnia zgłoszenia. 

Portretowe selfie w dziennym świetle, na wprost, patrząc w obiektyw. Bez żadnych filtrów. Bez okularów. Bez nakrycia głowy.

Panie - bez makijażu, w rozpuszczonych włosach tak, żeby widoczna była długość włosów

attachments.ocrText: May be an image of 2 people and text that says 'SZUKAMY EPIZODYSTEK! Film "Jan Bo" 11.10 Warszawa Panie ok 20-30 at Zgłoszenia na adres Ewelina.wika@podtytulem.pl PODI TYTUŁEM'

Hej alle sammen

Jeg søger en mandlig model til en kampagnevideo for vores rygsæk-brand. Der er ingen replikker, da videoen får musik og effekter som lydside, så det handler mest om tilstedeværelse og udtryk foran kameraet.

Optagelserne foregår i Århus. Projektet er på frivillig basis, men du får naturligvis det færdige materiale, som du også kan bruge til din egen portfolio.

Hvis det lyder som noget for dig, så kontakt mig over e-mail: Carlsjensen@icloud.com

På forhånd tak
Carl Schmidt Jensen

**Statister søges (ulønnet)**

Hej alle, 

Vi søger 3 statister til vores kortfilm FLYT DIG i alderen 60-100, køn er underordnet. 

**LOGLINE**

En konfliktsky ung mand bliver udnyttet af sine venner og ignoreret af sin familie. Da hans rebelske fætter hjælper ham med at flytte, må han indse, at frihed ikke bare handler om at bryde ud – men om at turde definere sine egne grænser.

Optagelserne foregår i tilst tirsdag d. 14 oktober fra 9-17. Der vil være forplejninger på set.

Skriv til mig på messenger eller til *sara774g@gmail.com* ved interesse.

Venlig Hilsen, Sara Riahi

CASTING CALL 

Production Company: GreenHouse Films Production 

Project Type: UCF BFA Short Film 

Union Status: Non-Union 

Pay Status: Unpaid Projected 

Shooting Dates: TBD 

Shooting Location: Orlando area 

Summary: A lonely girl shunned by her school finds comfort in plants and in the one friend who truly sees her. 

This is an unpaid project - copy and credit will be given to all involved. This is a non-union production. 

Character Breakdowns: 

MONOMAY: Female, 18+ (must be able to pass as a teenager), A teen girl marked by facial scars and iris coloboma, finds purpose and comfort in tending to her beloved plants. 

JASON: Male, 18+ (must be able to pass as a teenager), The school's "Golden Boy" athlete, hides his insecurities behind charisma. 

FAN CLUB: Any gender, 18+ (must be able to pass as a teenager), A group of students that fawn over Jason and seek his attention. 

How to Submit: Please send an email to greenhousefilmsproduction@gmail.com to reserve a time slot for auditions.

OR

Fill out this Google form: 
https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSeN2krq62Mec2KpTeJrleyIirLMgRBfIJkdh2N6B6q_VwMk3Q/viewform?usp=dialog

items.text:
CASTING CALL – Independent Short Film (LONDON)

We are casting for an upcoming student short film exploring obsession, ambition, and the dark side of the ballet world.

Production: Student film via The American University of Rome

Director: Maxine Sutton

Cinematographer: Georgia Blackson

Shooting Dates: December 12–19

ROLES

NATASHA (Lead)

Female, 18–28

Ballet-trained (advanced preferred)

Must convey vulnerability, intensity, and psychological depth

Strong acting, presence, and physical performance required

Slavic accent preferred.

Pay: 250€ flat rate for entire production

RUDOLPH

Male, 25–40

Dance experience preferred

Embodies both beauty and cruelty — a man who inspires awe, fear, and complete submission.

Slavic accent preferred.

Pay: 250€ flat rate for entire production

SYNOPSIS

Natasha, a talented but tormented ballerina, navigates a high-stakes audition that tests the limits of her physical and psychological endurance. As she strives for perfection under the watchful eye of the enigmatic Rudolph, the line between reality and terror begins to blur, forcing her to confront the true cost of ambition.

TO APPLY

CASTING CALL – Independent Short Film (LONDON)

We are casting for an upcoming student short film exploring obsession, ambition, and the dark side of the ballet world.

Production: Student film via The American University of Rome

Director: Maxine Sutton

Cinematographer: Georgia Blackson

Shooting Dates: December 12–19

ROLES

NATASHA (Lead)

Female, 18–28

Ballet-trained (advanced preferred)

Must convey vulnerability, intensity, and psychological depth

Strong acting, presence, and physical performance required

Slavic accent preferred.

Pay: 250€ flat rate for entire production

RUDOLPH

Male, 25–40

Dance experience preferred

Embodies both beauty and cruelty — a man who inspires awe, fear, and complete submission.

Slavic accent preferred.

Pay: 250€ flat rate for entire production

SYNOPSIS

Natasha, a talented but tormented ballerina, navigates a high-stakes audition that tests the limits of her physical and psychological endurance. As she strives for perfection under the watchful eye of the enigmatic Rudolph, the line between reality and terror begins to blur, forcing her to confront the true cost of ambition.

TO APPLY

Please complete the audition form and send it, along with a headshot, to: maxineclairesutton@gmail.com

items.text: Registration for this FREE webinar now open!

sharedPost.text:
I’ve been a model and actor for over 30 years, and as a certified mindset coach, I’ve also had the privilege of helping my daughter strengthen her mindset and grow her career with co-star, supporting, and supporting lead roles in projects for Paramount +, CBS, Hallmark, and more. Most recently, she appears as Rachel in Amazon Prime’s Top 10* *show* The Runarounds*.

﻿

I've been asked a lot over the years to share my experience and help other parents and young actors along on their acting journeys; that’s why I’m hosting a **free webinar on October 19** where you'll learn:
* Mindset strategies I taught my daughter (and use with my actor clients)
* The realities of building a career in acting—what most people *don’t*tell you
* The pros and cons of pursuing an acting degree
* Strategies we've used to open up audition and booking opportunties
* PLUS: get the inside scoop as my daughter shares her experience on *The Runarounds*: from first audition to being on set.

🎟️ Don't wait! Get all the details and save your spot here → [[Register Now]](https://campaign-statistics.com/link_click/e9VEqJ-gpxZ2D6-4ysUg9/a85533005915d0327bef8a6796583a43)

﻿

📅 **Date: October 19, 2025 **

🕔 **Time:** **4:00pm-5:30pm EST**

﻿

While this webinar is geared towards young actors & their parents, **actors of all levels **will benefit from this session. We will have an open, honest conversation that gives you clarity, direction, and encouragement as you navigate the acting journey.

﻿

Hope to see you there!

items.text:
🎬 Casting Call – Student Short Film

Production Title: Baggage

Director: Kole Jackson 

Role: Protagonist – Old Man

Requirement: Male actor in his 50s or 60s, preferably with a beard. Tall and skinny physique.

Shooting Dates: 18th – 19th September

As this is a passion-driven student short film, the role is unpaid, but catering will be provided throughout the shoot days.

Synopsis:

In a world where emotional burdens are physical baggage, an old man struggles to carry his load through a park. He longs to climb a sunlit hill but is held back by his heavy suitcases. He repeatedly rejects the help of a mysterious, baggage-free blonde man who offers him a pair of scissors to cut the rope binding him to his past. After a failed attempt to build a shelter from his bags and a collapse that leaves him injured, the old man finally accepts the scissors. Realizing he has the power to choose his path, he cuts the rope, freeing himself from his burden. The blonde man vanishes, and the old man, now unencumbered, finally climbs the hill, symbolizing his newfound freedom.

📧 If interested, please reach out to:

Kole Jackson (Director)– kole.jackson.m@gmail.com

Ahad Khan (Assistant Director)– ahadg8@gmail.com

After a failed attempt to build a shelter from his bags and a collapse that leaves him injured, the old man finally accepts the scissors. Realizing he has the power to choose his path, he cuts the rope, freeing himself from his burden. The blonde man vanishes, and the old man, now unencumbered, finally climbs the hill, symbolizing his newfound freedom.

**CASTING VIDEO – MANN UM DIE 40 – HANDWERKSBIER**
## 

Sind Sie ein Mann um die 40, natürlich und kamerafreundlich?

Sie sprechen **fließend Deutsch** (Pflicht) und können sich mit unserem Team auf **Französisch oder Englisch**verständigen?

Wir suchen einen Darsteller für einen Werbedreh zur Erstellung von **Videoinhalten für die sozialen Netzwerke** einer **handwerklich gebrauten Biermarke**.

📍 **Ort**: Lausanne, Schweiz

🕐 **Dauer**: Halber Drehtag

📅 **Datum**: Wochenende **16.–17. Oktober 2025**

💰 **Vergütung**: 100 € 

👉 **Bewerbung bitte mit**:

📸 Ein paar **aktuelle Fotos**

🎤 Einem kurzen **Vorstellungsvideo** (ca. 30 Sekunden) auf Deutsch

📩 **Bewerbungen und Fragen** bitte per Privatnachricht

## **CASTING VIDÉO – HOMME QUARANTAINE – BIÈRE ARTISANALE**

Vous êtes un homme d’une quarantaine d’années, naturel et à l’aise devant la caméra ?

Vous parlez **allemand couramment** (impératif), et vous pouvez communiquer en **français ou en anglais** avec nos équipes ?

Nous recherchons un figurant pour un tournage publicitaire destiné à la création de **contenus vidéos pour les réseaux sociaux** d’une **marque de bière artisanale**.

📍 **Lieu** : Lausanne, Suisse

🕐 **Durée** : 1 demi-journée de tournage

📅 **Date** : week-end du **16-17 octobre 2025**

💰 **Rémunération** : 100 € 

👉 **Pour candidater, merci d’envoyer** :

📸 Quelques **photos récentes**

🎤 Une courte **vidéo de présentation** (30 sec environ) en allemand

📩 **Candidatures et questions** par message privé

## 
## **VIDEO CASTING – MAN IN HIS 40s – CRAFT BEER**

Are you a man in your 40s, natural and comfortable on camera?

Do you speak **fluent German** (mandatory) and can communicate with our team in **French or English**?

We are looking for a background actor for a commercial shoot to create **video content for the social media channels** of a **craft beer brand**.

📍 **Location**: Lausanne, Switzerland

🕐 **Duration**: Half-day shoot

📅 **Date**: Weekend of **October 16–17, 2025**

💰 **Compensation**: 100 €

👉 **To apply, please send**:

📸 A few **recent photos**

🎤 A short **introduction video** (around 30 seconds) in German

📩 **Applications and questions** via private message

**Casting Calls - Standard Posting Format**

***CU Denver Student Film Casting Call***

Title: **Wolf Tickets**

Genre: Drama, True Crime

**Logline:** A florist becomes convinced that her boyfriend, an ex-felon, poses a deadly threat to her and her unborn child, sparking a Rashomon-style tale of paranoia, alienation, and tragedy.

**Synopsis:** A pregnant woman, Vivienne, is murdered by her lover, Anthony, an ex-con with a dark past. Through two distinct narratives, it is revealed how this tragedy came to be. Vivienne’s perspective reveals how fear and miscommunication can distort our perceptions; over the course of two months, we see Antony quickly becoming the monster that he once was. Meanwhile, Antony’s story exposes the devastating consequences of alienation and desperation

Main Roles: 

**Vivienne: **Vivienne is the protagonist of Wolf Tickets. A brown, female, florist in her early 30s. She fits the “broken optimist archetype. In her past, she had a brief fling with her employee, Anthony, an ex-convict. After experiencing a major epiphany stemming from the news that she’s pregnant, she begins to distance herself from Anthony - the result is catastrophic and leads to her eventual death.

**Anthony: **Anthony is the antagonist of Wolf Tickets. A male ex-convict in his early 30s is employed at a flower shop. He fits the “dreamer bound by reality” archetype. Anthony exudes charm but struggles to adapt to life outside of prison, finding solace in his relationship with Vivienne. After parting ways with her, Anthony begins to feel increasingly isolated and lost. With no clear direction or confidence, he’s suddenly overcome with the urge to repeat his past mistakes.

Writer/Director: Daniel Moreno

Producer: Emily Ball

Production Type: Student Film

Contact Information: For more information or questions prior to auditions, please email Emily at tvdinnerstudios25@gmail.com

Run Time: 8 Minute Short Film

Compensation: Unpaid

Additional Compensation: Meals Provided, Film Credit, & Copy of Final Cut 

Union Status: Non-Union

**Audition Information:**
* Submit a Self-tape to the Google Form Linked Below by October 9th
* Callbacks: TBD
   * They will be held at the CU Denver Campus 

Please fill out this Google Form if you wish to audition

[[https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSegEF6rOSLKsuxeipIXUZYTcGrluRFoBeceC9YKOoSSIMwo4w/viewform?usp=header](https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSegEF6rOSLKsuxeipIXUZYTcGrluRFoBeceC9YKOoSSIMwo4w/viewform?usp=header)](https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSegEF6rOSLKsuxeipIXUZYTcGrluRFoBeceC9YKOoSSIMwo4w/viewform?usp=header)

**Shooting Schedule:** October. 25th - October 27th & November 16th/17th (Times TBD)

**Filming Location:**
* Arvada, CO.
* Denver, CO.
* Westminster, CO.

Link to Sides: [https://drive.google.com/file/d/1CtgTTGsdSs-B6wew23imvIFsoH_ILsas/view?usp=sharing](https://drive.google.com/file/d/1CtgTTGsdSs-B6wew23imvIFsoH_ILsas/view?usp=sharing)

items.text:
**AUDITION NOTICE FROM PUTNEY THEATRE COMPANY**

**THE SEAFARER**

**by Conor McPherson**
**Sunday 26 October, 3pm**
**Monday 27 October, 7pm***

*If successful, you will be asked to attend a recall on Wednesday 29 October at 7pm

**Performances:**
**Tuesday 17 February 2026 – Saturday 21 February 2026, Putney Arts Theatre **

**AUDITION INFORMATION:**

For the audition you will be asked to perform either a selected monologue or short scene from the play. You may be asked to perform it a second time with some direction or with another auditionee.

All the characters in the play are Irish. All the characters, except for Mr Lockhart, come from Baldoyle, north of Dublin. Mr Lockhart could be from anywhere in Ireland.

When auditioning you should be able to show an ability and familiarity with an Irish accent, although we don’t expect it to be perfect at this point. Unless of course you are from North Dublin!

**Please contact the director on *****[ian@nickhernbooks.co.uk](https://www.putneyartstheatre.org.uk/mailto:%20peterpanto2025@gmail.com)*****  for audition pieces and any further information required.**

**ABOUT THE PLAY:**

A supernatural tale on a dark winter’s evening…

It’s nearly Christmas Eve and Sharky has returned to Dublin to look after his blind brother, Richard. As the two men rattle around their old house, they are joined by local layabouts Ivan and Nicky - and a stranger, new to town, the mysterious Mr Lockhart.

Over a night fuelled by alcohol and resentment, a game of cards is on the table. But the cost of losing may be higher than anyone imagines…

From Conor McPherson, award-winning author of The Weir and Girl from the North Country, comes a blackly funny, haunting tale of family and friendship, steeped in whiskey and stirred by regret and the need for redemption.

**CAST BREAKDOWN:**

Five Men aged 35-65 (ages in brackets are the possible age range for the parts).
* **Sharky**: On the wagon. A man who has lost in life and love but is struggling to be better. Trying to hold it together but lacking in the confidence he once had. (35 - 45)
* **Richard:** A big drinker. Recently blinded. A dishevelled, fetid old rogue. Irascible, childish and demanding but with a whiff of Irish charm. (50 - 65) 
* **Ivan: **A big man. An innocent, but full of anxiety.  A hard drinker who suffers from the aftereffects of his imbibing. (35 - 45)
* **Nicky: **The local wide boy. Confident cocky, always on the up and on the lookout. Thinks he’s much better than he is. (30 - 40)
* **Mr Lockhart:** Enigmatic. A different class to the other men and something of a mystery to them. Sophisticated in comparison, he is possessed of a dark and dangerous edge. (50 - 60)

“Sparkling and suspenseful… McPherson is a born yarn-spinner” Guardian

“A realistic fantasy, a wide-awake nightmare. The writing is poetic, brutal, athletic, hilarious” Sunday Times

“Conor McPherson is the heir to the great Irish tradition of absorbing tale telling” Observer

“The finest dramatist of his generation” The Telegraph 

**Please contact the director on *****[ian@nickhernbooks.co.uk](https://www.putneyartstheatre.org.uk/mailto:%20peterpanto2025@gmail.com)*****  for audition pieces and any further information required.**

**PLEASE NOTE: this is an amateur production and therefore non-paid. **

**AUDITION NOTICE FROM PUTNEY THEATRE COMPANY**

**THE SEAFARER**

**by Conor McPherson**
**Sunday 26 October, 3pm**
**Monday 27 October, 7pm***

*If successful, you will be asked to attend a recall on Wednesday 29 October at 7pm

**Performances:**
**Tuesday 17 February 2026 – Saturday 21 February 2026, Putney Arts Theatre **

**AUDITION INFORMATION:**

For the audition you will be asked to perform either a selected monologue or short scene from the play. You may be asked to perform it a second time with some direction or with another auditionee.

All the characters in the play are Irish. All the characters, except for Mr Lockhart, come from Baldoyle, north of Dublin. Mr Lockhart could be from anywhere in Ireland.

When auditioning you should be able to show an ability and familiarity with an Irish accent, although we don’t expect it to be perfect at this point. Unless of course you are from North Dublin!

**Please contact the director on *****[ian@nickhernbooks.co.uk](https://www.putneyartstheatre.org.uk/mailto:%20peterpanto2025@gmail.com)*****  for audition pieces and any further information required.**

**ABOUT THE PLAY:**

A supernatural tale on a dark winter’s evening…

It’s nearly Christmas Eve and Sharky has returned to Dublin to look after his blind brother, Richard. As the two men rattle around their old house, they are joined by local layabouts Ivan and Nicky - and a stranger, new to town, the mysterious Mr Lockhart.

Over a night fuelled by alcohol and resentment, a game of cards is on the table. But the cost of losing may be higher than anyone imagines…

From Conor McPherson, award-winning author of The Weir and Girl from the North Country, comes a blackly funny, haunting tale of family and friendship, steeped in whiskey and stirred by regret and the need for redemption.

**CAST BREAKDOWN:**

Five Men aged 35-65 (ages in brackets are the possible age range for the parts).
* **Sharky**: On the wagon. A man who has lost in life and love but is struggling to be better. Trying to hold it together but lacking in the confidence he once had. (35 - 45)
* **Richard:** A big drinker. Recently blinded. A dishevelled, fetid old rogue. Irascible, childish and demanding but with a whiff of Irish charm. (50 - 65) 
* **Ivan: **A big man. An innocent, but full of anxiety.  A hard drinker who suffers from the aftereffects of his imbibing. (35 - 45)
* **Nicky: **The local wide boy. Confident cocky, always on the up and on the lookout. Thinks he’s much better than he is. (30 - 40)
* **Mr Lockhart:** Enigmatic. A different class to the other men and something of a mystery to them. Sophisticated in comparison, he is possessed of a dark and dangerous edge. (50 - 60)

“Sparkling and suspenseful… McPherson is a born yarn-spinner” Guardian

“A realistic fantasy, a wide-awake nightmare. The writing is poetic, brutal, athletic, hilarious” Sunday Times

“Conor McPherson is the heir to the great Irish tradition of absorbing tale telling” Observer

“The finest dramatist of his generation” The Telegraph 

**Please contact the director on *****[ian@nickhernbooks.co.uk](https://www.putneyartstheatre.org.uk/mailto:%20peterpanto2025@gmail.com)*****  for audition pieces and any further information required.**

**PLEASE NOTE: this is an amateur production and therefore non-paid. **

🎥✨ CASTING CALL – BACKGROUND ROLES ✨🎬

We are looking for actors and actresses of all ages to join us for one-day background roles in our upcoming war drama film “There Are No Children”. Check out our website for more info: https://tancfilm.netlify.app/

📌 Background Roles Needed:
 • Civilians (men, women, children)
 • Wounded civilians & refugees
 • Soldiers
 • Enemy soldiers

🎬 Production Dates:
 • October 25–26 (Principal)
 • November 1–2 (Principal)
 • November 8–9 (Principal)
 • December 6–7 (Pick-ups)

This is a powerful production that explores survival, innocence, and resilience during war. Background performers will help bring authenticity and emotion to the world of the story.

📍 Location: Los Angeles area

Compensation: This is an unpaid student production. Crafty/meals provided on set and film credit will be given.

💌 To apply, please send an email to tancproduction@gmail.com with: 
• your name
• age
• photo
• availability

Join us in bringing this important story to life!

Best Regards,
Iren Tovmasian

ROSTER CALL: ICT Productions (SAG-AFTRA & DGA Signatory)

My company, ICT Productions, is building a first-call roster across departments for upcoming narrative, branded, and live projects in Los Angeles.

We’re an award-winning company and I’ve personally managed $200M+ across network/broadcast productions (including the Super Bowl) and multiple films in active development.

This is not an invite for immediate work; it’s an invite to join our vetted roster we call before any public search.

Departments (all levels welcome):

Production (Producers, UPM/PM, Coordinators)
AD Dept
Script Supervisor
Camera
G&E
Sound
Art/Set Dec
Props
Construction/Scenic
Wardrobe
Hair/Makeup
Locations
Stunts/Intimacy
SFX
Medics/Safety
Transportation
Video/DIT
VFX
Post (Editorial/Color/Sound/Score)
EPK/BTS
Crafty/Catering
Security

Email: jake@ictproductions.com

Subject: ICT Roster - [NAME]

• Role(s) + union status
• Base day rate + kit notes (if any)
• IMDb / Reel / Portfolio
• Home-base ZIP
• Best contact info
• Note if open to student/ultra-low projects

We run professional, safety-first, union-aligned sets with clear paperwork and on-time pay. 

Equal opportunity; all backgrounds encouraged to submit.

Thanks! Looking forward to meeting you.

Jake Crossman, Producer
ICT Productions, Los Angeles, CA
(747) 528-7818
jake@ictproductions.com

We are now casting for our Halloween Party show .

The show will tour into community based venues, Nursing and Residential Homes, Day Centres.

We are seeking self-contained experienced hardworking singer/ performers who are keen to take quality musical shows to the community.

The Dates

Rehearsals –17th and 18th October in London

Playing Dates-20th -31st October-

We work Monday to Friday only.

The show is a one man/woman show so we are looking for experienced engaging performers with great singing voices,

We are looking for drivers with cars only

Please confirm where you are based in your application.

We offer £700 per week plus fuel on the road .

We are also casting our one man / woman musical show Winter Wonderland that will tour care homes and community based throughout December.

The show is production style show based on songs from the musicals Mary Poppins, White Christmas, Singing In The Rain, The Wizard Of Oz As well as traditional Christmas songs and carols, comedy routines and festive entertainment for all.

Dates

Rehearsals 24th -28th November

Playing dates 1st-23rd December

We perform two 60 minute shows 6 days a week.

We are offering 600 .00 per week fuel on the road and accommodation allowance when required.

MUST BE A DRIVER WITH A CAR

Please email details including a singing reel to

info@theentertainmentproviders.co.uk

Hi everyone! I'm casting 'All-Round Champion', a CSA & Emmy Award-winning reality sports competition series that brings together 10 of the best youth athletes from across North America and the UK. Each season, these incredible athletes represent 10 different sports and face the ultimate challenge: competing in each other's disciplines for the title of All-Round Champion!

If you know any talented athletes between the ages of 11 and 18 who would thrive in this environment, I'd love for you to share this opportunity with them!

Interested athletes can apply here: [https://allroundchampion7.castingcrane.com](https://allroundchampion7.castingcrane.com/) - please note the deadline for submissions is early November, so don't delay!

Watch our Season 6 trailer to get a feel for the show: [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=GXbmDbRjQ24](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=GXbmDbRjQ24)

Learn more about our production company: [https://blueantmedia.com/](https://blueantmedia.com/)

Email me your questions at [Jessica.mcgann@blueantmedia.com](mailto:Jessica.mcgann@blueantmedia.com)

Production Company: GreenHouse Films Production 

Project Type: UCF BFA Short Film 

Union Status: Non-Union 

Pay Status: Unpaid Projected 

Shooting Dates: TBD 

Shooting Location: Orlando area 

Summary: A lonely girl shunned by her school finds comfort in plants and in the one friend who truly sees her. 

This is an unpaid project - copy and credit will be given to all involved. This is a non-union production. 

Character Breakdowns: 

MONOMAY: Female, 18+ (must be able to pass as a teenager), A teen girl marked by facial scars and iris coloboma, finds purpose and comfort in tending to her beloved plants. 

JASON: Male, 18+ (must be able to pass as a teenager), The school's "Golden Boy" athlete, hides his insecurities behind charisma. 

FAN CLUB: Any gender, 18+ (must be able to pass as a teenager), A group of students that fawn over Jason and seek his attention. 

How to Submit: Please send an email to greenhousefilmsproduction@gmail.com to reserve a time slot for auditions.

CASTING CALL 

Production Company: GreenHouse Films Production 

Project Type: UCF BFA Short Film 

Union Status: Non-Union 

Pay Status: Unpaid Projected 

Shooting Dates: TBD 

Shooting Location: Orlando area 

Summary: A lonely girl shunned by her school finds comfort in plants and in the one friend who truly sees her. 

This is an unpaid project - copy and credit will be given to all involved. This is a non-union production. 

Character Breakdowns: 

MONOMAY: Female, 18+ (must be able to pass as a teenager), A teen girl marked by facial scars and iris coloboma, finds purpose and comfort in tending to her beloved plants. 

JASON: Male, 18+ (must be able to pass as a teenager), The school's "Golden Boy" athlete, hides his insecurities behind charisma. 

FAN CLUB: Any gender, 18+ (must be able to pass as a teenager), A group of students that fawn over Jason and seek his attention. 

How to Submit: Please send an email to greenhousefilmsproduction@gmail.com to reserve a time slot for auditions.

OR

Fill out this Google form: 
https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSeN2krq62Mec2KpTeJrleyIirLMgRBfIJkdh2N6B6q_VwMk3Q/viewform?usp=dialog

items.text:
📣🎬 Casting Call – Short Mockumentary Film 

We are casting for ‘A Race with Ian Hitchworth’, a 3-minute mockumentary short film made as part of our final year at UWE Bristol. The film will be shot in Bristol in the week commencing 3rd November 2025 (exact dates TBC). This is a student project, unpaid, but with expenses covered. The film is intended for university showcase and festival submission.

Story:�Ian Hitchworth, son of a respected track runner, was once a rising sprint star. Years later, he resurfaces in a humiliating viral TikTok, and a small documentary crew captures his desperate bid to matter again—culminating in a shambolic charity race. Told in a deadpan, mockumentary style, the film mixes awkward comedy with moments of vulnerability as Ian’s arrogance clashes with his insecurities.

Roles:
Ian Hitchworth (Lead)�25, male. Wannabe track star with inflated self-belief and fragile confidence. To the camera, he’s arrogant, overconfident, and insists on being taken seriously — but cracks show through awkward silences and moments of panic. Actor must have strong comedic timing, improvisational instincts, and be comfortable with physical comedy (running, awkward costume, frustrated energy). Needs to balance deadpan humour with flashes of real vulnerability.

Interviewer (Supporting)�Any age/gender. Calm, inquisitive presence behind the camera, provoking Ian with offhand questions and blunt corrections. Think Nick Broomfield style: slightly awkward, matter-of-fact, not intentionally funny but often humorous through honesty. Delivery should be dry and understated. Voice-only, but may appear briefly on camera.

Race Official / Athletes (Supporting & Extras)�18–40, any gender. Includes a race official who ushers Ian onto the track (Small Speaking Role), plus authentic-looking athletes for the race sequence. Non-speaking, but must look natural on a track.

Apply by: 27th Ocotber 2025�To Apply: Please send a headshot, CV (or Spotlight/Mandy link), and any showreel/self-tape to Scarlet2.Gerry@live.uwe.ac.uk

We're casting for our magical Christmas Grotto experience in the Milton Keynes and Bedford area and we’re on the lookout for a charismatic, professional Mother Christmas to join the team!

📍 Location: 2 venues across MILTON KEYNES & BEDFORD
MK44 3QP & MK17 8UE
📆 Contract: December 2025
💸 Rate: £20 per hour

• Entry-level acting skills

• Basic script work and immersive performance ability

• Must absolutely love Christmas!

sharedPost.text:
Casting Call

Production: Mother's Ruin, by Steve Bird (Back by popular demand!)

The story so far in the life of Liverpool comedian Garry Skyner, one of Britain's first- born victims of the Thalidomide medical disaster. Steve Birds play is a moving and emotional, yet hard hitting play about the highs, lows, struggles and sheer determination of a loving Mother and her son who refused to be beaten by the Government and company that profited from this medical disaster.

We are looking for a talented female actor playing range 20-30ys, who is from Liverpool or can do a convincing accent, for the lead role of Frances, Gary's Mum.
Frances is a spirited, humourous woman, who whilst having a heart of gold, has an inner strength, is tough, and fights for her child and what is right.
If you believe you are what we are looking for please send you CV and headshot to elainestewart46@yahoo.com 

Auditions to take place on Sunday 21st September 1pm-3pm at a Liverpool venue to be disclosed on receipt of CV, and a script will be provided. 

Performances will take place at the Epstein Theatre on 27th and 28th February 2026.

You must be available for rehearsals Sundays 1pm- 4pm (in Liverpool) starting 2nd November.
*This is a profit share production

items.text:
My name is Luke Kenyon, and I’m a film student at SAE Liverpool. We’re currently working on a new short film project titled Last Night and are looking to cast two male-identifying actors (mid twenties)to join our team. This project is Non paid but we will be providing travel expenses as well as catering 

Synopsis -

On the anniversary of his best friend’s suicide, Aaron plans to end his own life. He ignores his mothers phone calls and edges closer towards his own end, until he unexpectedly hears a knock at his apartment front door. His best friend, Ben, appears in an attempt to make amends and guide Aaron away from darkness. This intimate drama, through one final, raw conversation, forces Aaron to choose between following the same path that Ben took a year ago, or answering the call that could save him.

Aaron:

Aaron, mid 20's, slightly introverted and reserved. A complicated character with a lot going on in his mind. His low confidence makes it hard for him to open up to others about his feelings, especially about the loss of his best friend (Ben), who meant the world to him. He loves music and even used to play in a band with Ben. 

Ben:

Ben, mid 20's, soft and sensitive personality. His battles with his own mental health has led him to an unfortunate end, which ultimately, has hurt someone very close to him (Aaron), although this was never his intention. Ben’s aim is to make some sort of amends from his past actions and to help Aaron not make the same mistake that he did. 

If you have any questions about the project or roles, please don’t hesitate to get in touch — I’m happy to provide more information.

If you  are interested in applying, please use one of the provided links below or alternatively email me at 120206uk@saeinstitute.edu with your details, previous work, or portfolio. (Including heat shots) please provide which role you are applying for 

Thank you very much for your time We look forward to hearing from you!

Kind regards,

Luke Kenyon

Film Student, SAE Institute

https://www.backstage.com/casting/last-night-student-film-3019197/

https://www.starnow.com/casting/last-night-3021254/

https://www.mandy.com/aa/project/3021242/last-night/

items.text:
Rainhill Garrick Society are performing ‘ Habeus Corpus’ by Alan Bennett on February 12th-14th 2026.

Alan Bennett’s Habeus Corpus is set some time in the Seventies and follows the lives of the Wicksteed family. The story follows Dr and Muriel Wicksteed as they both seek pleasure and fun outside of their marital relationship. The farcical play is very fast paced, incredibly funny and occasionally surreal. The bumbling sex-obsessed British characters such as the virginal vicar, the ﬂat chested spinster, the peering doctor, his frustrated wife and of course a bra salesman man all come together in this bizarre and thoroughly entertaining story.

Parts available:-

Dennis Wicksteed - the hypochondriac son of Dr Wickseed, (20-30)

Felicity Rumpers - young, nubile, upper class  (20-30)

Constance Wicksteed - the sister of Dr Wicksteed, flat chested and sex starved, (20+) 

Sir Percy Shorter - chairman of the BMA, quite upper class and not too tall (Mid 40s+

Play read through Tuesday 21st October at 7.30 in Rainhill Village Hall

Auditions- Thursday 23rd October at 7.30 Rainhill Village Hall 

Rehearsals are on Tuesdays and Thursday evenings 7.30-9.30 and the 3 Sundays prior to the performance.

Audition pieces are available on request. 

We are an amateur group so the roles are unpaid, but we are a well respected group of 83 years standing who enjoy great support from a large dedicated audience. 

The play is great fun with some slapstick and music but with some poignant moments that say a lot about relationships.

For further information, contact: sophiebrogan99@gmail.com

Following the incredible success of our award-winning short film 'The Hit' at the Short Film Festival Manchester, Marble Academy and Solefuge Media Productions are thrilled to announce auditions for our upcoming low-budget short film, ‘Hotel Rent,’ set to film in Manchester early next year.

We're on the lookout for six talented actors to bring this project to life! While these roles are unpaid, we will cover travel expenses and provide meals.
Plus, this is a fantastic opportunity to enhance your showreel or portfolio!

If you’re passionate about acting and eager to dive into a vibrant creative environment, we want to hear from you!
Please send us a direct message or an email to marbleacademy@hotmail.com. Share a bit about yourself, the role that excites you the most, and what draws you to that character.
Auditions are in-person on Saturday, November 22nd, in Swinton, Manchester.

Don’t forget to include a link to your Spotlight or Backstage profile. We can’t wait to find the incredible talent that will shine in our project!

With ONLY 3 WEEKS LEFT, make sure you’ve got your tickets as the countdown has begun for our highly anticipated Actors and Filmmakers Networking Event on Sunday, October 26th! Are you ready to take a transformative step in your career? This is your moment!

 

For years, Marble Academy has proudly facilitated these events. Following the incredible turnout at our June gathering, which drew over 90 attendees, we hope to build on this success. Just imagine the possibilities!

 

Get ready to immerse yourself in a space filled with talented actors, visionary directors, influential producers, and skilled crew members, all eager to share insights and forge meaningful connections. This is your chance to meet the kind of people who could help bring your next big project to life.

 

Mark your calendars for Sunday, October 26th, from 2 PM to 6:30 PM at HOME Mcr, located at 2 Tony Wilson Place, Manchester, M15 4FN.

 

🎟️ Secure your ticket now and be part of something special: [https://www.eventbrite.co.uk/e/actors-and-filmmakers-networking-event-tickets-1509159349239](https://www.eventbrite.co.uk/e/actors-and-filmmakers-networking-event-tickets-1509159349239) 

I can’t wait to see you there

STILL FEEL LIKE YOUR NOT MOVING FORWARD AS AN ACTOR ??? 

Most actors spend years in classes and never learn the real fundamentals that get them work.

At The Foundry Acting Studio, we don’t just “talk” about acting…. we train you like a professional. Our students go from their very first class to being on set in real films, learning more in weeks than many do in years.

Because you’re not a number here. You’re a future storyteller….. and we’ll show you how to become the actor casting directors remember.

🌟 Spotlight Approved • 🎥 SAG Recognised • 🎬 Real Films • 🎭 Real Results

Message us now for in person , online or one to one classes.

sharedPost.text:
Film zostanie wysłany na ogolnolicealny Fresh Form film festiwal, sa dwie reżyserki, w tym ja, z małym doświadczeniem ale wielkim zapałem. Mamy kamerę i stroje. Nie jest to płatne, można powiedzieć hobbistyczne, ale na pewno będzie to ciekawa przygoda. Okolice Warszawy, Piaseczna. Dni nagrywek są elastyczne 

Film jest obyczajowy, opowiada o grupie nastolatków zmagających się z problemami w rodzinie, z używkami i chorobą. Film opiera się na scenach rozmów, drogi i ‚gonitwy’. jest bardzo emocjonalny i pełen pasji.

Fajnie jakby zgłoszeni mieli styl bliski alternatywnemu, rockowemu (wielkim plusem byłaby umiejętność gry na gitarze) Szukamy przede wszystkim chłopaka 170-190cm z kręconymi włosami, grający rolę najlepszego przyjaciela głównego bohatera który stara się pomóc w leczeniu jego matki.

Poboczne role to postać chłopaka o podobnym wzroście, jasne proste lub falowane włosy, oraz jeszcze dwójki chłopaków, bez większych wymagań (jeden lepiej by było jakby miał długie włosy, hipisowski styl)

Naprawdę doceniam każdego chętnego, jesteśmy bardzo zaangażowane w tworzenie, a scenariusz jest naprawdę ambitny.

**WARSZAWA 11 października**

**film fabularny - Rola Epizodyczna**

**Stawka: 1000 zł**

Do roli epizodycznej w filmie fabularnym JAN BO szukam młodej atrakcyjnej kobiety, która wystąpi w scenie - **topless**.

Bez kontrowersji. Jeden z bohaterów budzi się obok pięknej dziewczyny. Jest do połowy przykryta.

**Do zgłoszenia proszę załączyć wizytówkę jako link do YouTube.**

Ponieważ gramy lata 80te mamy nieuniknione wytyczne charakteryzacji:
* brak tatuaży 
* bez tuneli w uszach, kolczyków w wardze, nosie czy brwiach
* paznokcie TYLKO naturalne.
* bez permanentnych makijaży, doklejonych rzęs i  ingerencji medycyny estetycznej

**ZGŁOSZENIA**

Poproszę na adres: **ewelina.wika@podtytulem.pl**

W tytule: **GIRL**

W treści: imię i nazwisko, wiek, nr telefonu, miejscowość + wymiary: wzrost, klatka, pas, biodra, rozmiar ubrania i buta + wizytówka

W załączniku: ZDJĘCIE TWARZY I SYLWETKI (ubrane): tylko z dnia zgłoszenia.
* Portretowe selfie w dziennym świetle, na wprost, patrząc w obiektyw. Bez żadnych filtrów. Bez okularów. Bez nakrycia głowy.
* Bez makijażu, w rozpuszczonych włosach tak, żeby widoczna była długość włosów

items.text:
***CASTING CALL FOR STUDENT FILM!!!***

***UNPAID & NON-UNION***

Location: Vancouver, BC

Film Dates: November 14th, 15th, & 16th with 2 rehearsals to be scheduled after casting

Casting "Confession", a student short film set in the late 1950s about a closeted devout Catholic who confesses his secret love for his priest during confession, only to discover the priest feels the same way.

Father Elias D'Arcy (white male, 25-35) - A devout Catholic priest who has been the head of Jacob’s church for a few years now, developing a close relationship with his parish. He came from a poor family, the child of Irish immigrants and the eldest of 6, he’s always had a nurturing nature to him and often helped others to the detriment of his own mental capacity. A closeted homosexual, Elias has delved deep into his religion and joined the priesthood to stave off any romantic connection, unwilling to come to terms with his sexuality.

Jacob McCarthy (white male, 25-35) - A devout Catholic and closeted gay man, his struggles with his raised religion and his sexuality being the catalyst for his story. He forced himself to marry a girl he was raised going to church with to promote a sense of normalcy and to please his family as the eldest child and only son expected to carry on the family name and reputation. He's unhappy with the life he chose to live for other people, feeling as though no one really knows him for who he truly is.

Actors will be compensated with a copy of the film, credit, and a meal every day of filming.

For audition scheduling and sides, please contact a.culp@infocusfilmschool.com

items.text:
**WARSZAWA **

**10, 11, 13, 14 października**

**film fabularny**

Na kolejne dni filmu **JAN BO** i już jedne z ostatnich szukam Statystów jak poniżej. Przeczytajcie proszę uważnie wytyczne charakteryzacji.

**10 PAŹDZIERNIKA (piątek):**
* **MŁODZIEŻ NA PRÓBIE MUZYCZNEJ 18-25 LAT **- jedna scena, wnętrze. Głównie dziewczyny. Stawka: 120 zł gotówka po planie

**11 PAŹDZIERNIKA (sobota):**
* **POKOJÓWKA**- kobieta ok. 30-40 lat. Stawka 180 zł gotówką po planie (przymiarki stacjonarne: 60 zł + 120 zł za dzień zdjęciowy). Przymiarki w piątek 10.10 na Chełmskiej po 14:00 

**13 PAŹDZIERNIKA (poniedziałek):**
* **GOŚCIE BARU / PRZECHODNIE - wiek ok. 20-55 lat. **Jedna scena, godziny popołudniowe.** **Stawka 120 zł gotówką po planie
* **STRAŻNICY GRANICZNI - mężczyźni ok. 30-50 lat**. Jedna scena. Poproszę wymiary w zgłoszeniu. Stawka 140 zł gotówką po planie
* **STRAŻNIK GRANICZNY Z OWCZARKIEM NIEMIECKIM **- jak wyżej. Jedna scena. Stawka 180 zł gotówką po planie.
* **KELNERKA **- **kobieta ok. 20-35 lat**.Jedna scena. Stawka 120 zł gotówką po planie

**14 PAŹDZIERNIKA (wtorek):**
* **KOBIETA NA SPACERZE Z PSEM** - wiek bez znaczenia. Psiak nie może być rasowy. Kundle będą najlepsze. Poproszę zdjęcie psa również. **Jedna scena nocna. 240 zł przelewem**

Ponieważ gramy lata 80te mamy nieuniknione wytyczne charakteryzacji:

**Dla wszystkich:**
* brak tatuaży w widocznych miejscach (ręce również, na nogach u pań też odpadają)
* bez tuneli w uszach
* kolczyki w nosie, brwiach czy wardze trzeba wyjąć na zdjęcia

**Panowie:**
* bez wygolonych boków i bez włosów ścinanych maszynką, bez zarostów od barbera
* długie włosy super
* łysi panowie niestety odpadają

**Panie:**
* paznokcie TYLKO naturalne. 
* bez permanentnych makijaży, doklejonych rzęs i innych ingerencji współczesnych kosmetologii

**ZGŁOSZENIA**

Poproszę na adres: **dominika@podtytulem.pl**

W tytule: **JB + wybrane daty**

W treści: imię i nazwisko, wiek, nr telefonu, miejscowość + wymiary: wzrost, klatka, pas, biodra, rozmiar ubrania i buta

W załączniku: ZDJĘCIE TWARZY I SYLWETKI: tylko z dnia zgłoszenia.

Portretowe selfie w dziennym świetle, na wprost, patrząc w obiektyw. Bez żadnych filtrów. Bez okularów. Bez nakrycia głowy.

Panie - bez makijażu, w rozpuszczonych włosach tak, żeby widoczna była długość włosów

Panowie - dodatkowo zdjęcie z profilu

**WARSZAWA **

**10, 11, 13, 14 października**

**film fabularny**

Na kolejne dni filmu **JAN BO** i już jedne z ostatnich szukam Statystów jak poniżej. Przeczytajcie proszę uważnie wytyczne charakteryzacji.

**10 PAŹDZIERNIKA (piątek):**
* **MŁODZIEŻ NA PRÓBIE MUZYCZNEJ 18-25 LAT **- jedna scena, wnętrze. Głównie dziewczyny. Stawka: 120 zł gotówka po planie

**11 PAŹDZIERNIKA (sobota):**
* **POKOJÓWKA**- kobieta ok. 30-40 lat. Stawka 180 zł gotówką po planie (przymiarki stacjonarne: 60 zł + 120 zł za dzień zdjęciowy). Przymiarki w piątek 10.10 na Chełmskiej po 14:00 

**13 PAŹDZIERNIKA (poniedziałek):**
* **GOŚCIE BARU / PRZECHODNIE - wiek ok. 20-55 lat. **Jedna scena, godziny popołudniowe.** **Stawka 120 zł gotówką po planie
* **STRAŻNICY GRANICZNI - mężczyźni ok. 30-50 lat**. Jedna scena. Poproszę wymiary w zgłoszeniu. Stawka 140 zł gotówką po planie
* **STRAŻNIK GRANICZNY Z OWCZARKIEM NIEMIECKIM **- jak wyżej. Jedna scena. Stawka 180 zł gotówką po planie.
* **KELNERKA **- **kobieta ok. 20-35 lat**.Jedna scena. Stawka 120 zł gotówką po planie

**14 PAŹDZIERNIKA (wtorek):**
* **KOBIETA NA SPACERZE Z PSEM** - wiek bez znaczenia. Psiak nie może być rasowy. Kundle będą najlepsze. Poproszę zdjęcie psa również. **Jedna scena nocna. 240 zł przelewem**

Ponieważ gramy lata 80te mamy nieuniknione wytyczne charakteryzacji:

**Dla wszystkich:**
* brak tatuaży w widocznych miejscach (ręce również, na nogach u pań też odpadają)
* bez tuneli w uszach
* kolczyki w nosie, brwiach czy wardze trzeba wyjąć na zdjęcia

**Panowie:**
* bez wygolonych boków i bez włosów ścinanych maszynką, bez zarostów od barbera
* długie włosy super
* łysi panowie niestety odpadają

**Panie:**
* paznokcie TYLKO naturalne. 
* bez permanentnych makijaży, doklejonych rzęs i innych ingerencji współczesnych kosmetologii

**ZGŁOSZENIA**

Poproszę na adres: **dominika@podtytulem.pl**

W tytule: **JB + wybrane daty**

W treści: imię i nazwisko, wiek, nr telefonu, miejscowość + wymiary: wzrost, klatka, pas, biodra, rozmiar ubrania i buta

W załączniku: ZDJĘCIE TWARZY I SYLWETKI: tylko z dnia zgłoszenia.

Portretowe selfie w dziennym świetle, na wprost, patrząc w obiektyw. Bez żadnych filtrów. Bez okularów. Bez nakrycia głowy.

Panie - bez makijażu, w rozpuszczonych włosach tak, żeby widoczna była długość włosów

Panowie - dodatkowo zdjęcie z profilu

Do you have a passion for all things scary?

A walk that sends shivers down spines?

Or maybe you just love being part of the chaos behind the scares?

Fear Columbus in Columbus, Ohio is HIRING IMMEDIATELY for:

🩸 Haunted House Actors (unleash your inner monster, clown, or demon)

🩸 Event Staff (keep the terror running smoothly from the shadows)

✨ No experience? No problem. We’ll train you to scare like a pro.

✨ evening shifts + the most fun job you’ll ever have.

✨ Be part of one of the largest haunted attractions in Ohio.

This is your chance to join our spooky family and create memories (and nightmares) that guests won’t forget!

💀 Apply NOW and come be a part of all the spooky fun! 

⚡ Don’t wait — the screams start soon and spots are filling FAST! 

Click the link below or in my bio for info on what it entails working here and for the application! 

Can't wait to see you <3

[https://fearcolumbus.com/applications/](https://fearcolumbus.com/applications/)

RUSH CASTING for "A-Z Murder Mystery"

This Project is a LIVE Murder Mystery Experience where everyone had a motive and the audience has to find the killer. (Like "Glass Onion"). Male talent should be a great storyteller and enjoy improv. 

Production Date: Saturday, November 15th

LENNY: 
African American Male
Age: 30-40’s; possibly older.

A confident, cocky Black male, Lenny is the flashy, fast-talking owner of one of the hottest music labels in the game. Strong, commanding presence.

To Request Sides:

📧 Submit to: PolishedImagesCasting@gmail.com

Subject line: A2Z - Aud926 - LENNY– your full name
(Ex: A2Z – Aud926 – LENNY– Polished Images)

 ✍🏽  Body of email: 
Contact info: Name, Email, Phone#
Social Media Links:
October Availability:

 🖇️ Attach:
Current Photo (Headshot)
Headshot holding something w/ Today’s Date

Sides will be sent upon receipt. 

Other details and self-tape instructions: A Self-tape of the sides in Vertical format. Please record in Vertical (Portrait) format. Standing 

Full Submission Details:
Your Submission is due by 7pm, Friday, September 26th.

This is a PAID position. 

Good Luck! 

#Audition #Auditions  #ATL #Atlanta

items.text:
Hello! We are shooting an unpaid improvised short film next week from the 15th to the 18th of October based on the concept for our feature film SOPHIE, and we are looking for an actor for one for the lead roles, to play a charismatic pubcrawl guide (25-35, Male) with a dark side. Shooting will take place on the 15th, 16th, 17th and 18th of October, all night shoots.

If you're interested in knowing more details please send me your showreel or a short introductory video of you and your acting experience, to vasco.cinema.2018@gmail.com.

Sinopsis: On a weekend escape to Copenhagen, Sophie reunites with an old friend and spirals through a night of fleeting connections, as she’s forced to confront the cost of trying to feel anything at all.

GENRE:** Psychological Thriller

LOCATION:** Milwaukee, WI, USA

PRODUCTION DATES:** Late October – Early November 2025

---

*Christopher* is a haunting psychological thriller exploring mental health, ambition, and relationships. As the protagonist spirals into a surreal unraveling of self, those closest to him must confront what is real, and what is fractured.

---

**AMARA VEX**

**CLARA HAWTHORNE*

Due to high demand, we’ve added another date for the adults-only Cass Casting Workshop and it’s already booking up fast!

📅 Friday 19th October
🕕 6:00pm–8:30pm (UK time)
📍 Live on Zoom
🎟 Limited spaces only a small group of actors will be accepted to ensure everyone gets focused time and feedback.

This is your chance to work with Cassandra Moore, the casting director behind Cass Casting, known for her work across commercials, film, and TV  and for her brilliant eye for discovering fresh talent. Cass brings a wealth of experience, insight, and no-nonsense feedback that actors rarely get to hear directly.

Whether you’re looking to sharpen your commercial casting technique, build confidence in the room, or stand out in your next self-tape, this session is for you.

🎟 Book now before spaces go: LINK IN BIO

📩 Once booked, you’ll be sent Zoom details ahead of the session.

Let me know if you have any questions  and I can’t wait to see you there!
